SIMPLE: squabble
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squabble
<hw>Squab"ble</hw> <pr>(skw⟦ocr⟧b"b'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Squabbled</conjf>
<pr>(-b'ld)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Squabbling</conjf>
<pr>(-bl⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. dial. Sw. <ets>skvabbel</ets>
a dispute, <ets>skvappa</ets> to chide.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
contend for superiority in an unseemly manner; to scuffle; to struggle;
to wrangle; to quarrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To debate peevishly; to dispute.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sense of these propositions is very plain, though logicians
might <qex>squabble</qex> a whole day whether they should rank them
under negative or affirmative.</q> <rj><qau>I. Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To dispute; contend; scuffle; wrangle; quarrel;
struggle.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squabble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squabble
<hw>Squab"ble</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Print.)</fld> <def>To
disarrange, so that the letters or lines stand awry or are mixed and
need careful readjustment; -- said of type that has been set
up.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squabble</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Squabble
<hw>Squab"ble</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A scuffle; a wrangle; a
brawl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squabbler</ent>⟦br⟧
